    • Method Detail

      • calcInstructions

        public static java.util.List<java.lang.Double> calcInstructions​(double x,
                                                                double y,
                                                                double w,
                                                                double h)
        This method takes as input, an x coordinate, a y coordinate, a width, and a height, all indicating the location of an identified object in a matrix. Using these values, it will estimate a distance between the camera and the object, and the angle that the camera is viewing the object at. The function will then generate a list of movements that should be applied to the arm's joins, such that the arm will be in a position where it would grab the object were it to squeeze. These instructions will be in the form of a list of doubles, each double indicating the angle their corresponding joint should rotate. This list is returned to the caller.
        Since:
        2019-10-09
